# Git Workflow Instructions for All Teams

## Branch Creation
To create a new branch, use the following command:
```
git checkout -b <branch-name>
```

## Branch Switching
To switch to an existing branch, run:
```
git checkout <branch-name>
```

## Basic Git Commands
### Check Status
To check the status of your repository, use:
```
git status
```

### Add Changes
To stage changes for commit, run:
```
git add <file-name>
```

### Commit Changes
To commit your changes, use:
```
git commit -m "Your commit message here"
```

### Push Changes
To push your changes to the remote repository, use:
```
git push origin <branch-name>
```